 even as that experience continues to unfold. It regards our current situation not for what it may become in the future, but rather as a moment of mass uncertainty and existential hesitation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xPolitical aspects. 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xPsychological aspects. 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xSocial aspects. 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Essays.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228020820?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228020820423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228020820/original  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles